  "abstract": "The Dumas method, a rapid and precise technique for determining total carbon and nitrogen in soils, involves high-temperature combustion under oxygen-rich conditions with detection of evolved gases using TC-TN analyzers. This method provides accurate measurements of TC and TN, making it a preferred approach for soil fertility and nutrient analysis.",
  "title": "Estimation of Total Carbon and Total Nitrogen in Soil Samples by Dumas Method",
